1
00:00:00,570 --> 00:00:04,879
[Never Too Late]

2
00:00:04,879 --> 00:00:09,160
Director Zhang. A month ago, Nami launched its Cloud series.
[Episode 1]

3
00:00:09,160 --> 00:00:13,299
They have already done two rounds of promotion, with an in-depth user experience.

4
00:00:13,299 --> 00:00:16,960
- If we launch now, won't we be copying—
- What are we copying?

5
00:00:16,960 --> 00:00:19,980
They've launched the Cloud series, so we'll launch a Dark Cloud series.

6
00:00:19,980 --> 00:00:21,840
Are they the only cloud in the sky?

7
00:00:21,840 --> 00:00:23,640
Jiang Xile!

8
00:00:24,519 --> 00:00:26,720
- Jiang Xile!
- Here.

9
00:00:28,380 --> 00:00:31,019
- Dr. Ding, the next patient, Jiang Xile, is coming in.
- Jiang Xile,

10
00:00:31,019 --> 00:00:33,560
- Okay.
- Are you listening to me?
- Thank you.

11
00:00:33,560 --> 00:00:37,139
Director Zhang, this name isn't suitable. Please reconsider it.

12
00:00:37,139 --> 00:00:41,400
In any case, I'm giving you two days. I don't care how you do it,

13
00:00:41,400 --> 00:00:44,819
but by Monday, I need to see the design draft for Dark Cloud.

14
00:00:44,819 --> 00:00:48,159
- Director Zhang, after all, what we're selling is lingerie.
- Take off your coat.

15
00:00:48,159 --> 00:00:50,240
The name Dark Cloud is unsuitable, right?

16
00:00:50,240 --> 00:00:52,240
Whether it's suitable or not isn't for you to decide.

17
00:00:52,240 --> 00:00:54,480
Hurry and bring your draft back to me.

18
00:00:54,480 --> 00:00:56,559
Dr. Ding, the patient is ready.

19
00:00:56,559 --> 00:00:59,599
Okay, let her unfasten her bra.

20
00:00:59,599 --> 00:01:02,440
Nurse, why is it a male doctor?

21
00:01:02,440 --> 00:01:05,520
What's wrong with a male doctor? Hurry and unfasten it.

22
00:01:06,300 --> 00:01:10,660
Jiang Xile. Jiang Xile! Are you listening to me?

23
00:01:10,660 --> 00:01:15,060
They've already done two rounds of promotion, but you haven't even finished the draft yet.

24
00:01:15,060 --> 00:01:17,460
Do you even want this job?

25
00:01:17,460 --> 00:01:20,580
The first demand of a woman for lingerie is comfort.

26
00:01:20,580 --> 00:01:24,860
Today, I'm wearing Nami's Cloud. The lace steel ring is very tight.

27
00:01:24,860 --> 00:01:27,860
We really don't need to copy them.

28
00:01:30,579 --> 00:01:33,320
Just unfasten it. No need to take it off.

29
00:01:35,775 --> 00:01:38,159
[Dr. Ding Ran, Breast Surgeon]

30
00:01:38,159 --> 00:01:40,350
Ding Ran?

31
00:01:50,744 --> 00:01:53,780
- Jiang Xile. Jiang Xile?
- It can't be this much of a coincidence, can it?

32
00:01:54,680 --> 00:01:56,330
Hello!

33
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:05,648
No need to lie down.

34
00:02:10,024 --> 00:02:14,240
Same first name, same surname. He looks a bit similar, and he is also a doctor.

35
00:02:28,860 --> 00:02:32,179
Ding Ran. Ding Ran!

36
00:02:32,179 --> 00:02:34,619
Ding Ran...

37
00:02:34,619 --> 00:02:36,408
Ding Ran.

38
00:02:40,840 --> 00:02:42,516
What's up?

39
00:02:42,516 --> 00:02:47,719
Nothing, I heard you had a cold. I prepared some hot water for you.

40
00:02:49,419 --> 00:02:53,559
Jiang Xile, I'm not so sick to not be able to pour water.

41
00:03:03,239 --> 00:03:04,968
What are you doing?

42
00:03:06,019 --> 00:03:07,799
Ding Ran.

43
00:03:12,699 --> 00:03:14,860
There are stars in your eyes.

44
00:03:14,860 --> 00:03:17,039
They're shining.

45
00:03:33,220 --> 00:03:35,080
Pull up your shirt.

46
00:03:38,180 --> 00:03:40,140
Pull up your shirt.

47
00:03:40,900 --> 00:03:43,820
I asked you to pull up your shirt.

48
00:03:49,979 --> 00:03:53,060
Have you felt anything abnormal in your breasts before?

49
00:03:54,939 --> 00:03:57,660
Have you eaten any stimulating food recently?

50
00:04:00,579 --> 00:04:02,416
Does it hurt here?

51
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:08,220
What about here?

52
00:04:08,220 --> 00:04:11,500
It doesn't hurt. I feel like dying.

53
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:20,840
I just took a preliminary look.

54
00:04:20,840 --> 00:04:22,400
Your situation might be—

55
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:24,240
Thank you, Doctor.

56
00:04:25,164 --> 00:04:28,360
- Are you okay?
- Sorry. It's been ten years.

57
00:04:28,360 --> 00:04:30,879
A girl changes a lot from childhood to adulthood. He can't possibly recognize me.

58
00:04:30,879 --> 00:04:34,300
- He didn't recognize me. He can't possibly recognize me.
- Jiang Xile.

59
00:04:42,539 --> 00:04:44,540
You forgot your underwear.

60
00:04:47,799 --> 00:04:49,719
Director Zhang, you're looking for me, right?

61
00:04:49,719 --> 00:04:51,840
I'll be right there. I'll be right there.

62
00:04:51,840 --> 00:04:53,576
Jiang Xile.

63
00:04:58,210 --> 00:05:00,350
[Wang Yue]

64
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:08,199
Hello, may I ask…

65
00:05:08,199 --> 00:05:12,079
Miss Jiang, didn't you move out?

66
00:05:16,519 --> 00:05:21,420
Baby, I forgot to tell you that we moved.

67
00:05:21,420 --> 00:05:23,480
Moved? Why did we move?

68
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:26,040
Didn't I tell you?

69
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:31,580
Three months ago, I bumped into my first love from when I was eighteen.

70
00:05:31,580 --> 00:05:35,600
You did say, but what does that have to do with us moving?

71
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:39,499
I have decided to get married.

72
00:05:39,499 --> 00:05:41,260
Get married?

73
00:05:41,260 --> 00:05:43,239
- I...
- Don't worry, Baby.

74
00:05:43,239 --> 00:05:45,220
I didn't get married on impulse.

75
00:05:45,220 --> 00:05:49,100
It's not a rush to get married, but a passionate elopement.

76
00:05:49,100 --> 00:05:51,800
All right, all right. Come over quickly.

77
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:53,499
Mom.

78
00:05:53,499 --> 00:05:57,480
Miss. Jiang, Ms. Xiao left a piece of luggage with us.

79
00:05:57,480 --> 00:05:59,160
- This is my suitcase.
- Yes.

80
00:05:59,160 --> 00:06:00,860
Thank you.

81
00:06:04,539 --> 00:06:09,720
Mom made me stay to go find her with you.

82
00:06:21,840 --> 00:06:24,760
Senyun, you're amazing.

83
00:06:24,760 --> 00:06:27,460
You even know how to draw on cakes.

84
00:06:27,460 --> 00:06:29,820
Wait until Xile moves in.

85
00:06:30,420 --> 00:06:33,899
I will draw a good one of our family of four.

86
00:06:49,559 --> 00:06:53,259
Thank goodness my mom left you here, or else…

87
00:07:00,939 --> 00:07:03,280
Luckily, I ran fast.

88
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:15,339
We would probably never see each other again in this life.

89
00:07:33,039 --> 00:07:36,480
Mom, our first meeting is to have dinner at their house.

90
00:07:36,480 --> 00:07:41,359
What's wrong with that? Anyway, we're going to be a family soon.

91
00:07:41,359 --> 00:07:43,120
- Dinner is ready.
- Baby.

92
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:48,110
This is my fiancé, Ding Senyun, Mr. Ding.

93
00:07:48,110 --> 00:07:49,640
Hi.

94
00:07:53,340 --> 00:07:57,400
Let's not wait. Xile, let's eat before the food gets cold.

95
00:07:57,400 --> 00:07:59,420
- Okay.
- Let's eat.

96
00:08:01,599 --> 00:08:05,040
By the way, Baby, I'm planning to marry Uncle Ding.

97
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:09,520
Considering that you and Xiao Ran also need to become each other's family and need some time to adjust.

98
00:08:09,520 --> 00:08:12,199
So I decided to move next door.

99
00:08:12,199 --> 00:08:14,020
But I didn't notify you in advance.

100
00:08:14,020 --> 00:08:16,220
You're not mad at me, are you?

101
00:08:16,220 --> 00:08:18,320
How could I be?

102
00:08:20,920 --> 00:08:24,000
Xiao Ran? Who is Xiao Ran?

103
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:26,040
Xiao Ran is my son.

104
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:28,020
He is a doctor.

105
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:39,160
Uncle Ding, your son wouldn't also have the surname Ding, would he?

106
00:08:43,339 --> 00:08:44,680
What a coincidence!

107
00:08:44,680 --> 00:08:47,079
My son also surnamed Ding.

108
00:08:48,060 --> 00:08:51,439
Baby, why are you asking such a question?

109
00:08:51,439 --> 00:08:53,439
I…

110
00:08:53,439 --> 00:08:56,139
It can't be this coincidence, can it?

111
00:08:57,359 --> 00:09:01,460
So is he called Ding Xiaoran or Ding Ran?

112
00:09:01,460 --> 00:09:03,500
Ding Ran.

113
00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:05,540
Speaking of which, it's such a coincidence.

114
00:09:05,540 --> 00:09:08,660
You and Ding Ran were classmates.

115
00:09:08,660 --> 00:09:12,700
Back in your senior year, I specially told Xile to take care of Xiao Ran.

116
00:09:12,700 --> 00:09:14,159
So, Xile, are you close?

117
00:09:14,159 --> 00:09:16,140
Yes, are you close?

118
00:09:16,140 --> 00:09:18,820
It's been so many years. You probably won't recognize each other.

119
00:09:18,820 --> 00:09:22,739
That's right. I told Xiao Ran you were coming for dinner today.

120
00:09:22,739 --> 00:09:26,340
- I told him to come back early. He should be here by now.
- It's okay.

121
00:09:26,340 --> 00:09:27,460
What a coincidence.

122
00:09:27,460 --> 00:09:30,379
Mom, I suddenly feel a little unwell.

123
00:09:30,379 --> 00:09:33,360
I'm done eating, Uncle Ding. I'll go first.

124
00:09:37,500 --> 00:09:40,140
At that time, I only had one thought.

125
00:09:40,140 --> 00:09:42,799
Run away fast.

126
00:09:45,379 --> 00:09:48,160
Oh, no!

127
00:10:24,099 --> 00:10:25,699
Baby.

128
00:10:31,219 --> 00:10:34,900
Such courtesy for a first meeting.

129
00:10:39,839 --> 00:10:45,679
Baby, if you had hit your mouth just now, you would have lost your front teeth.

130
00:10:52,259 --> 00:10:55,919
Mom, let's talk about something else.

131
00:10:56,900 --> 00:11:03,240
Right, Baby, Xiao Ran, after Senyun and I met again, we have a new life.

132
00:11:04,919 --> 00:11:06,480
Mom, are you pregnant?

133
00:11:06,480 --> 00:11:08,540
Dad, did you go to the hospital for a check-up?

134
00:11:08,540 --> 00:11:10,319
No, no. You misunderstood.

135
00:11:10,319 --> 00:11:12,340
What we meant was,

136
00:11:12,340 --> 00:11:17,599
after meeting Xiao Baobei, our lives are like starting anew.

137
00:11:18,219 --> 00:11:20,020
Xiao Baobei?

138
00:11:20,020 --> 00:11:22,760
My mom's surname is Xiao. Her first name is Baobei.

139
00:11:22,760 --> 00:11:24,820
"Bao" means baby, and "Bei" means bud.

140
00:11:24,820 --> 00:11:26,059
That's right, that's right.

141
00:11:26,059 --> 00:11:31,019
My name is easy to misunderstand, and the way I speak often leads to misunderstanding.

142
00:11:31,019 --> 00:11:32,620
Don't misunderstand me.

143
00:11:32,620 --> 00:11:35,140
Mom, what you just said scared me.

144
00:11:35,140 --> 00:11:38,360
I thought at my age, I would have a younger sister.

145
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:41,639
Although you don't have a younger sister, you have a younger brother.

146
00:11:41,639 --> 00:11:43,360
Who?

147
00:11:50,979 --> 00:11:54,179
If I remember correctly, she and I are of the same year.

148
00:11:54,179 --> 00:11:57,140
You are of the same year, so what? Xile is three months older than you.

149
00:11:57,140 --> 00:12:00,780
Besides, we're going to be a family soon. Just call her sister.

150
00:12:00,780 --> 00:12:03,620
Uncle Ding, it's just three months. No need, no need.

151
00:12:03,620 --> 00:12:06,200
Where does she look like she could be an elder sister?

152
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:10,260
You brat, how is Xile not like an elder sister?

153
00:12:10,260 --> 00:12:13,680
She has been rash and careless since high school.

154
00:12:13,680 --> 00:12:16,760
After all these years, she didn't change at all.

155
00:12:18,259 --> 00:12:21,260
Ding Ran, you bumped my head and didn't even apologize.

156
00:12:21,260 --> 00:12:23,240
Now you're saying I'm rash?

157
00:12:23,240 --> 00:12:25,020
I was just coming home normally.

158
00:12:25,020 --> 00:12:27,160
Who knew you would rush over so quickly?

159
00:12:27,160 --> 00:12:30,000
I rushed over because I found out you were Uncle Ding's son.

160
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:32,340
Ding Ran, sit straight.

161
00:12:38,339 --> 00:12:41,380
Baobei, Ding Ran usually doesn't talk much at home.

162
00:12:41,380 --> 00:12:43,100
I don't know what's the matter with him today.

163
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:44,359
It's okay, it's okay.

164
00:12:44,359 --> 00:12:46,020
I'm my dad's son.

165
00:12:46,020 --> 00:12:47,919
Is there a problem?

166
00:12:47,919 --> 00:12:49,840
If it were you, wouldn't you feel awkward?

167
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:52,339
We're not just ordinary high school classmates.

168
00:12:52,339 --> 00:12:55,520
On the day of the graduation reunion, I told you…

169
00:12:57,320 --> 00:13:01,940
Baby, at the graduation reunion, what did you say to Xiao Ran?

170
00:13:03,184 --> 00:13:06,759
- That day she said—
- Ding Ran and I have been at odds since high school.

171
00:13:06,759 --> 00:13:10,559
On the day of the graduation reunion, he told me…

172
00:13:10,559 --> 00:13:13,620
What did you say to Xile that day?

173
00:13:13,620 --> 00:13:15,320
Ding Ran.

174
00:13:17,680 --> 00:13:19,099
I want to date you.

175
00:13:19,099 --> 00:13:20,839
What do you think?

176
00:13:22,382 --> 00:13:27,170
♫ Let's leave the past in the past ♫

177
00:13:27,899 --> 00:13:33,459
♫ Let's not forgive each other ♫

178
00:13:33,459 --> 00:13:35,110
Jiang Xile.

179
00:13:35,110 --> 00:13:37,680
♫ This is how it ends, I'll leave, ♫

180
00:13:37,680 --> 00:13:40,440
I don't have time to participate in your boring life.

181
00:13:41,567 --> 00:13:44,349
♫ ... all right? ♫

182
00:13:45,279 --> 00:13:47,280
He said...

183
00:13:48,680 --> 00:13:51,360
he really hated me.

184
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:53,840
- Are you sure those were my exact words?
- That's what you meant.

185
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:56,220
Why do you always misinterpret my meaning?

186
00:13:56,220 --> 00:13:59,280
Ding Ran, sit straight.

187
00:14:03,019 --> 00:14:08,079
X-Xile, Ding Ran has been stubborn since he was a kid.

188
00:14:08,079 --> 00:14:09,760
Don't mind him.

189
00:14:09,760 --> 00:14:14,060
Xile is also stubborn. There must be some misunderstanding.

190
00:14:14,060 --> 00:14:16,779
Mom, there's no misunderstanding.

191
00:14:16,779 --> 00:14:18,899
I also really dislike him.

192
00:14:18,899 --> 00:14:21,779
But don't worry, it won't affect you and Uncle Ding.

193
00:14:21,779 --> 00:14:25,139
You can get married and have a baby if you want to.

194
00:14:25,139 --> 00:14:29,010
Uncle Ding, Mom, I'm done eating. I'll get going.

195
00:14:29,780 --> 00:14:30,560
You...

196
00:14:30,560 --> 00:14:34,340
Baby. Baby, the door is this way.

197
00:14:38,099 --> 00:14:40,999
Do you know the door code?

198
00:14:40,999 --> 00:14:44,120
Senyun, I'll go back first.

199
00:14:48,019 --> 00:14:51,979
You brat have been bullying Xile since high school.

200
00:14:53,900 --> 00:14:57,199
Who taught you to bully girls, huh?

201
00:14:57,760 --> 00:14:59,680
Dad, I didn't bully her.

202
00:14:59,680 --> 00:15:01,400
That day was…

203
00:15:03,740 --> 00:15:06,440
- Forget it.
- Well, what happened on that day?

204
00:15:06,440 --> 00:15:09,580
I don't care what happened. From today on, be nicer to Xile.

205
00:15:09,580 --> 00:15:11,879
She's your elder sister.

206
00:15:12,972 --> 00:15:14,079
I'm full.

207
00:15:14,079 --> 00:15:16,039
Well, I'm talking to you.

208
00:15:16,039 --> 00:15:17,780
What's this attitude?

209
00:15:17,780 --> 00:15:20,120
Who wants her to be my elder sister?

210
00:15:27,211 --> 00:15:29,833
[Graduation Keepsake]

211
00:15:32,500 --> 00:15:35,939
How can I encounter him after so many years?

212
00:15:39,540 --> 00:15:41,660
Baby, are you asleep?

213
00:15:41,660 --> 00:15:43,779
Yes.

214
00:15:53,460 --> 00:15:56,000
Uncle Ding saw you didn't much at dinner.

215
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:58,379
He specially cooked noodles for you.

216
00:15:58,379 --> 00:16:00,819
Get up, have a bite while it's hot.

217
00:16:06,339 --> 00:16:08,400
It smells good.

218
00:16:09,039 --> 00:16:13,779
I look at Uncle Ding. He doesn't look like your first love at all.

219
00:16:13,779 --> 00:16:16,180
Mom, your aesthetics can't be like this.

220
00:16:16,180 --> 00:16:18,299
Are you after his money or his house?

221
00:16:18,299 --> 00:16:19,720
Nonsense.

222
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:22,460
This house is rented by us.

223
00:16:22,460 --> 00:16:27,380
Well, Uncle Ding might look a bit fierce,

224
00:16:27,380 --> 00:16:31,759
but he's a gentle and good person.

225
00:16:32,320 --> 00:16:37,519
Looking at Ding Ran's character, his father doesn't seem to be gentle and good.

226
00:16:38,039 --> 00:16:41,839
You only understand people after living with them.

227
00:16:41,839 --> 00:16:44,919
How can you judge them by their looks?

228
00:16:44,919 --> 00:16:48,399
This first love is the most wonderful.

229
00:16:48,399 --> 00:16:51,200
Baby, do you have a first love?

230
00:16:59,119 --> 00:17:00,759
Yes.

231
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:04,320
Where is he now?

232
00:17:04,320 --> 00:17:05,960
He's dead.

233
00:17:07,660 --> 00:17:11,440
Died young? So pitiful.

234
00:17:11,440 --> 00:17:13,579
How did he die?

235
00:17:17,420 --> 00:17:24,020
Mom, why didn't you tell me earlier that the man you were going to marry was my high school classmate's father?

236
00:17:25,660 --> 00:17:32,299
I... I was afraid you would have such a big reaction, so I didn't dare to tell you.

237
00:17:32,299 --> 00:17:34,860
You and Uncle Ding are going to get married in two months.

238
00:17:34,860 --> 00:17:37,159
Why move now?

239
00:17:37,159 --> 00:17:39,980
How far is our old house from here?

240
00:17:39,980 --> 00:17:44,280
Also, I was thinking you and Xiao Ran would eventually become a family.

241
00:17:44,280 --> 00:17:48,860
You should meet and adapt earlier, so it won't be awkward when you meet.

242
00:17:48,860 --> 00:17:51,320
Isn't it awkward to meet now?

243
00:17:51,320 --> 00:17:54,420
Who wants to be neighbors with their high school male classmate?

244
00:17:55,839 --> 00:18:00,240
If you really can't get along with Xiao Ran,

245
00:18:00,240 --> 00:18:06,079
Uncle Ding and I can also not get married.

246
00:18:10,959 --> 00:18:14,659
Didn't you say it's a first love reunited after thirty years?

247
00:18:14,659 --> 00:18:17,799
It's like a new life. Can you bear to give it up?

248
00:18:19,979 --> 00:18:21,580
All right.

249
00:18:21,580 --> 00:18:23,540
It won't affect you and Uncle Ding.

250
00:18:23,540 --> 00:18:27,960
Although Ding Ran is really difficult to deal with, I just won't see him.

251
00:18:27,960 --> 00:18:30,180
Don't let him hear you badmouth him.

252
00:18:30,180 --> 00:18:33,880
Ding Ran's room is just one wall away from yours.

253
00:18:33,880 --> 00:18:36,059
This jerk Ding Ran…

254
00:18:36,739 --> 00:18:40,200
This jerk Ding Ran lives next door to me?

255
00:19:16,464 --> 00:19:19,680
[Graduation Keepsake]

256
00:19:39,547 --> 00:19:45,804
♫ I look at you from behind ♫

257
00:19:45,804 --> 00:19:48,760
Classmates, Go in, classmates.
[Ten Years Ago, Xiangyang Middle School Graduation Ceremony]

258
00:19:48,760 --> 00:19:50,319
We're starting to take photos.

259
00:19:50,319 --> 00:19:52,980
Classmates, line up by height.

260
00:19:52,980 --> 00:19:54,660
Tall ones stand at the back.

261
